        "title": "World (The Price of Love)",
        "content": "{{Short description|1993 single by New Order}}\n{{Distinguish|World in Motion}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = World (The Price of Love)\n| cover      = World_-_New_Order_-_CD_Single.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[New Order (band)|New Order]]\n| album      = [[Republic (album)|Republic]]\n| released   = {{start date|1993|8|23|df=y}}<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Single Releases|magazine=[[Music Week]]|page=23|date=21 August 1993}}</ref>\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| length     = 3:38\n| label      = [[London Records|London]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/25394/new-order/|title=New Order &#124; full Official Chart History &#124; Official Charts Company|website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]]}}</ref>\n| writer     = \n* [[Bernard Sumner]]\n* [[Peter Hook]]\n* [[Stephen Morris (musician)|Stephen Morris]]\n* [[Gillian Gilbert]]<ref>[http://www.ascap.com/ace/search.cfm?requesttimeout=300&mode=results&searchstr=530383685&search_in=i&search_type=exact&search_det=t,s,w,p,b,v&results_pp=30&start=1 Ascap entry]</ref>\n| producer   = \n* New Order\n* [[Stephen Hague]]\n| prev_title = [[Ruined in a Day]]\n| prev_year  = 1993\n| next_title = [[Spooky (New Order song)|Spooky]]\n| next_year  = 1993\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|CXzs47qy2Pk|\"World (The Price of Love)\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''World (The Price of Love)'''\" is twenty-second single by English band [[New Order (band)|New Order]], released in August 1993 by [[London Records]] as the third single from their sixth studio album, ''[[Republic (album)|Republic]]'' (1993). Simply listed as \"World\" on the album, the subtitle \"The Price of Love\" was added for the single release, as it is repeated during the chorus. A 7:34 dance remix of the track by [[Paul Oakenfold]], called the \"Perfecto mix\", was included on many releases of the single and was used for an alternate edit of the video.\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was originally shot in April 1996. It was used for both the original version and an edit of the Perfecto remix of the song. Directed by [[Baillie Walsh]] and shot in [[Cannes]] with only 4 long [[steadicam]] shots, the video features the camera slowly journeying from the [[pier]] of the beach club of the exclusive luxury [[InterContinental Carlton Cannes Hotel|Carlton Hotel]] into the hotel itself, lingering on the faces of hotel guests. \n\nIt features the band only fleetingly – [[Peter Hook]] sits at a table on the beach club restaurant, [[Bernard Sumner]] stands overlooking the sea, and [[Stephen Paul David Morris|Stephen Morris]] and [[Gillian Gilbert]] pose for a photograph outside the [[Carlton Hotel, Cannes|Carlton Hotel]]; the photographer on the esplanade striking the 'Elvis' pose is percussionist David Armstrong, who was a session musician on the 'Republic' album.  This would be the last time the band would appear in a video until 2005's \"[[Jetstream (song)|Jetstream]]\".\n\n==Track listings==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing     = [[Gillian Gilbert]], [[Stephen Hague]], [[Peter Hook]], [[Stephen Morris (musician)|Stephen Morris]] and [[Bernard Sumner]]\n| headline        = CD 1: NUOCD 3 (UK and Europe)\n\n| title1          = World\n| note1           = [[Perfecto Records|Perfecto]] edit) (remixed by [[Paul Oakenfold]] and [[Steve Osborne]]\n| length1         = 4:02\n| title2          = World\n| note2           = radio edit\n| length2         = 3:39\n| title3          = World\n| note3           = Perfecto mix) (remixed by Paul Oakenfold and Steve Osborne\n| length3         = 7:33\n| title4          = World\n| note4           = Sexy Disco dub) (remixed by Paul Oakenfold and Steve Osborne\n| length4         = 5:56\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = CD 2: NUCDP 3 (UK and Europe)\n\n| title1          = World\n| note1           = Brothers in Rhythm mix) (remixed by [[Brothers in Rhythm]]\n| length1         = 8:03\n| title2          = World\n| note2           = Brothers Dubstrumental) (remixed by Brothers in Rhythm\n| length2         = 5:39\n| title3          = World\n| note3           = World in Action mix) (remixed by [[K-Klass]]\n| length3         = 5:51\n| title4          = World\n| note4           = Pharmacy dub) (remixed by K-Klass\n| length4         = 7:06\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 7-inch single: 857240.7 (Europe); cassette: NUOMC 3 (UK and Europe)\n\n| title1          = World\n| note1           = radio edit\n| length1         = 3:39\n| title2          = World\n| note2           = Perfecto edit) (remixed by Paul Oakenfold and Steve Osborne\n| length2         = 4:02\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = 12-inch single: NUOX 3 (UK and Europe)\n\n| title1          = World\n| note1           = Perfecto mix) (remixed by Paul Oakenfold and Steve Osborne\n| length1         = 7:33\n| title2          = World\n| note2           = Sexy Disco dub) (remixed by Paul Oakenfold and Steve Osborne\n| length2         = 5:56\n| title3          = World\n| note3           = Brothers in Rhythm mix) (remixed by Brothers in Rhythm\n| length3         = 8:03\n| title4          = World\n| note4           = World in Action mix) (remixed by K-Klass\n| length4         = 5:51\n}}\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Chart (1993)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=aus>{{cite Ryan|page=201}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|87\n|-\n{{single chart|Canadatopsingles|49|chartid=2270|access-date=7 November 2022}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canadadance|7|chartid=2301|access-date=7 November 2022}}\n|-\n|Europe ([[Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.worldradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1993/MM-1993-09-25.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=10|issue=39|date=25 September 1993|page=21|access-date=24 March 2024}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|45\n|-\n|Europe (European Hit Radio)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.worldradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1993/MM-1993-10-02.pdf|title=EHR Top 40|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=10|issue=40|date=2 October 1993|page=22|access-date=10 April 2024}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|23\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany|77|artist=New Order|song=World (The Price of Love)|songid=152965}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland2|27|artist=New Order|song=World (The Price of Love)}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|13|date=19930905}}\n|-\n|UK Airplay (''[[Music Week]]'')<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.worldradiohistory.com/UK/Music-Week/1993/Music-Week-1993-09-25.pdf|title=The Airplay Chart|magazine=[[Music Week]]|date=25 September 1993|page=30|access-date=29 April 2024}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|92|artist=New Order|access-date=7 November 2022}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardalternativesongs|5|artist=New Order|access-date=7 August 2017}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddanceclubplay|1|artist=New Order|access-date=7 November 2022}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddancesales|26|artist=New Order|access-date=7 November 2022}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{New Order}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:World (The Price Of Love)}}\n[[Category:1993 songs]]\n[[Category:1993 singles]]\n[[Category:New Order (band) songs]]\n[[Category:London Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Stephen Hague]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bernard Sumner]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Gillian Gilbert]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Peter Hook]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Stephen Morris (musician)]]"
