        "title": "Mor Karima",
        "content": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=May 2011}}\n{{one source|date=May 2011}}\n}}\n\n'''Mor Karima'''  is a [[Village#South Asia|village]] in Sidhwan Bet [[Mandal]] located in [[Ludhiana district]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], India. Mor Karima has a population of 1316 living in 216 households.<ref>\"http://ddws.gov.in/ddwsimis/RuralWaterSupply/reports/ReportYSRHabitationDistrict.aspx?districtId=0375&districtname=LUDHIANA {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724205826/http://ddws.gov.in/ddwsimis/RuralWaterSupply/reports/ReportYSRHabitationDistrict.aspx?districtId=0375&districtname=LUDHIANA |date=24 July 2011 }}\"</ref> The village is one of 3789 villages in Punjab that have a [[Scheduled castes and scheduled tribes|scheduled caste]] population of 40% and above.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.eci.nic.in/delim/Draft/punjab/Draft_English.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=31 May 2011 |archive-date=10 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210061136/http://eci.nic.in/delim/Draft/punjab/Draft_English.pdf |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nThe exact cartographic coordinates of Mor Karima are 30.83456, 75.60699. Other nearby villages within Sidwhan Bet Mandal are Sidhwan Bet, Abupura, [[Akuwal]], Aliwal, Amargarh Kaler, Baghian, Bahadarke, Baniewal,  Barsal, Bassian Bet, and Bhaini Araian. Mor Karima is {{convert|112|km|mi|sp=us}} from [[Chandigarh]], the capital of both Punjab and Haryana.\n\n==Archeological Findings==\nMedieval and terracotta artifacts from the [[Indus Valley Civilization|Harappan]] and [[Kushana]] civilizations have been found in Mor Karima, buried two meters underground in a large area of 50,000 square meters.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://asi.nic.in/nmma_reviews/Indian%20Archaeology%201980-81%20A%20Review.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=31 May 2011 |archive-date=8 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508072056/http://asi.nic.in/nmma_reviews/Indian%20Archaeology%201980-81%20A%20Review.pdf |url-status=dead }}</ref> These artifacts are from the Mature Harappan era (2600 - 1900 BCE).\n\n==Natural Resources==\n[[Salt petre]] is found in Mor Karima and appears on the ground as an alkaline efflorescence in the summer months. Every seven to ten days, three to four centimeters of the ground is scraped to encourage production of salt petre. Cloudy weather and rainfall during the harvest season negatively affects salt petre production.<ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YF70PN_uRu8C&q=%22mor+karima%22&pg=PA96 |title = Ground Water: Surveys and Investigation|isbn = 9788131304747|last1 = Mahajan|first1 = Gautam|year = 2009}}</ref>\n\nThere are two sources of safe water in Mor Karima which provide 1.8 litres per capita per day. There is significantly less water available for villages in Mor Karima than there are in other villages such as [[Narangwal]], whose water sources provide 39 litres per capacity per day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ddws.gov.in/ddwsimis/RuralWaterSupply/reports/ReportYSRHabitationDistrict.aspx?districtId=0375&districtname=LUDHIANA |title=ReportYSRHabitationDistrict |access-date=31 May 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724205826/http://ddws.gov.in/ddwsimis/RuralWaterSupply/reports/ReportYSRHabitationDistrict.aspx?districtId=0375&districtname=LUDHIANA |archive-date=24 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The Indian Government's Accelerated Rural Water Supply Programme has recognized Mor Karima as having a water status of Not Covered (NC) and in need of funding to provide adequate sources of clean water.\n\n==Education==\nSarkari Primary School is the only government primary school located in Mor Karima.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}} There is also a government medium school.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ssaludhiana.org/page25.htm |title=Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan - Ludhiana Office - SUDHAR |access-date=28 May 2011 |archive-date=27 August 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827201709/http://ssaludhiana.org/page25.htm |url-status=dead }}</ref> Some students attend Mahant Lachhman Dass (MLD) High School, a private English and Punjabi [[medium school]] located in [[Talwandi Kalan]], Ludhiana, Punjab.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mldschool.in/busoute.php |title=Welcome to MLD High School |access-date=28 May 2011 |archive-date=22 August 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110822072147/http://mldschool.in/busoute.php |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOf the 1212 persons living in Mor Karima at the time of the 2001 India Census, 883 persons were literate; 499 men and 384 women.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.voiceofbharat.org/ludhiana/view_results.asp?NAME=&sorttype=ASC&NAV=17&sortid=NAME|title = Avis employeur cic – formulaire d'avis de l'employeur et demande de remboursement|date = 27 January 2022}}</ref>\n\n==Religion==\nThere is 2 Gurudwaras in Village-\n*Gurudwara Singh Sabha\n*Gurudwara Ravidass Bhagat\n\n==Government and Infrastructure==\nThe [[sarpanch]] of Mor Karima is Gurpreet Kaur and Panch is Subedar Niranjan Singh, Kulwant Singh, and Bibi Gurdeep Kaur.<ref>http://www.qilaraipur.org/villagewhos.aspx?villageid=126 {{Dead link|date=March 2022}}</ref>\nMor Karima's pin/postal code is 142 023. The postal office that serves Mor Karima is Mor Karima Branch Office Post Office.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.machwan.com/all-india-pin-codes/Punjab.xls |title=Archived copy |access-date=26 October 2011 |archive-date=28 April 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110428100216/http://www.machwan.com/all-india-pin-codes/Punjab.xls |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThere are 63 Rural Household District Exchange Lines providing telephone services to Mor Karima.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tatateleservices.com/download/aboutus/ttsl/punjab_30-06-08.xls |title=Archived copy |access-date=26 October 2011 |archive-date=6 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106162812/http://tatateleservices.com/download/aboutus/ttsl/punjab_30-06-08.xls |url-status=dead }}</ref> The SDCA code for Mor Karima is 1624.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.callingludhiana.com/ludhiana-area-codes?sort=asc&order=SDCA|title = Area Codes for Ludhiana and Nearby Locations &#124; Call Ludhiana, India}}</ref>\n\n==Nearby Colleges==\n\n*LGC (4&nbsp;km)\n*LPC (4&nbsp;km)\n*Bajaj College Chaukimaan(4&nbsp;km)\n*CT University Sidhwan (5&nbsp;km)\n*GHG Khalda College Gurusar (12&nbsp;km)\n*GHG College Sidhwan Khurd( 7&nbsp;km)\n\n==Nearby markets==\n\n* Sowaadi Kalan Market (4&nbsp;km)\n*Mullanpur (8&nbsp;km)\n*Jagraon (9&nbsp;km)\n*Ludhiana (26&nbsp;km)\n*Chaukimaan (4&nbsp;km)\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|30|50|N|75|36|E|display=title|region:IN_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n{{Ludhiana district}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Ludhiana district]]"
