        "title": "Djamaa",
        "content": "{{Distinguish|Djema'a}}\n{{Redirect|Jamaa|the film|Journey to Jamaa|the fictional country|National Geographic Animal Jam}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Djamaa\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            = ﺟﺎﻣﻌﺔ\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        =Commune and town\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              = DZ 57 Djamaa.svg\n|mapsize                = 250px\n|map_caption            = Location of Djamaa commune within El M'Ghair Province\n|pushpin_map            = Algeria\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 300\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Djamaa within Algeria\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = {{flag|Algeria}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Provinces of Algeria|Province]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[El M'Ghair Province]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Algeria|District]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Djamaa District]]\n|subdivision_type3      = \n|subdivision_name3      = \n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|established_title      =  \n|established_date       = \n|area_magnitude         = \n|unit_pref                =Metric\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_land_km2            = \n|population_as_of               = 2008\n|population_footnotes           = <ref name=\"census2008\"/>\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               = 50916\n|population_density_km2         =\n|timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]] \n|utc_offset             =  +1\n|coordinates            = {{coord|33|32|N|6|0|E|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|elevation_m            = 41\n|elevation_ft           = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Djamaa''' ({{langx|ar|ﺟﺎﻣﻌﺔ}}) (also written '''Jama'a'''<ref name=\"statoids\"/>) is a town and [[Communes of Algeria|commune]] in [[El M'Ghair Province]], [[Algeria]]. According to the 2008 census it has a population of 50,916,<ref name=\"census2008\">{{cite web|title=Population: El Oued Wilaya |url=http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p1.pdf |publisher=Office National des Statistiques Algérie |access-date=12 February 2013 |language=fr |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513125205/http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p1.pdf |archive-date=13 May 2013 }}</ref> up from 37,438 in 1998,<ref name=\"statoids\">{{cite web|title=Algeria Communes|url=http://www.statoids.com/ydz.html|publisher=Statoids|access-date=9 March 2013}}</ref> with an annual growth rate of 3.1%.<ref name=\"census2008\"/>\n\n== Geography ==\nTo the east of Djamaa is a large area of palm plantations. The locality of [[Tigdidine]] lies amongst the palm trees. To the west the landscape is mostly [[arid]] and sandy, although there is another smaller palm plantation about {{convert|3|km|mi}} west of the town.\n\n== Climate ==\n\nDjamaa has a hot [[desert climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification]] ''BWh''), with very hot summers and mild winters, and very little precipitation throughout the year.\n\n{{Weather box\n| location = Djamaa\n| metric first = yes\n| single line = yes\n| width = auto\n| Jan high C = 16.8\n| Feb high C = 19.4\n| Mar high C = 23.4\n| Apr high C = 28.0\n| May high C = 33.0\n| Jun high C = 37.9\n| Jul high C = 41.5\n| Aug high C = 40.8\n| Sep high C = 35.7\n| Oct high C = 28.9\n| Nov high C = 21.9\n| Dec high C = 17.4\n| Jan mean C = 10.5\n| Feb mean C = 12.9\n| Mar mean C = 16.5\n| Apr mean C = 20.6\n| May mean C = 25.4\n| Jun mean C = 30.5\n| Jul mean C = 33.5\n| Aug mean C = 32.9\n| Sep mean C = 28.6\n| Oct mean C = 22.3\n| Nov mean C = 15.6\n| Dec mean C = 11.4\n| Jan low C = 4.2\n| Feb low C = 6.4\n| Mar low C = 9.6\n| Apr low C = 13.2\n| May low C = 17.9\n| Jun low C = 23.2\n| Jul low C = 25.5\n| Aug low C = 25.1\n| Sep low C = 21.6\n| Oct low C = 15.7\n| Nov low C = 9.4\n| Dec low C = 5.4\n| Jan precipitation mm = 8\n| Feb precipitation mm = 4\n| Mar precipitation mm = 12\n| Apr precipitation mm = 8\n| May precipitation mm = 5\n| Jun precipitation mm = 1\n| Jul precipitation mm = 0\n| Aug precipitation mm = 1\n| Sep precipitation mm = 6\n| Oct precipitation mm = 10\n| Nov precipitation mm = 10\n| Dec precipitation mm = 11\n| source 1 = climate-data.org<ref>{{cite web|title=Climate data for: Djamaa|url=http://en.climate-data.org/location/27464/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130703235600/http://en.climate-data.org/location/27464/|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 July 2013|publisher=climate-data.org|access-date=8 April 2013}}</ref>\n| date=March 2013}}\n\n== Transportation ==\n\nDjamaa has a station on the Biskra-Touggourt railway line. The N3 highway passes through the town, also connecting [[Biskra]] in the north to [[Touggourt]] in the south.\n\n== Education ==\n\n6.5% of the population has a tertiary education, and another 16.1% has completed secondary education.<ref>{{cite web|title=Structure relative de la population résidente des ménages ordinaires et collectifs âgée de 6 ans et plus selon le niveau d'instruction et la commune de résidence. |url=http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p6.pdf |publisher=Office National des Statistiques Algérie |access-date=13 February 2013 |language=fr |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513130809/http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p6.pdf |archive-date=13 May 2013 }}</ref> The overall literacy rate is 80.7%, and is 86.3% among males and 75.2% among females.<ref>{{cite web|title=Taux d'analphabétisme et taux d'alphabétisation de la population âgée de 15 ans et plus, selon le sexe et la commune de résidence . |url=http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p10.pdf |publisher=Office National des Statistiques Algérie |access-date=13 February 2013 |language=fr |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513124334/http://www.ons.dz/collections/w39_p10.pdf |archive-date=13 May 2013 }}</ref>\n\n== Localities ==\nThe commune of Djamaa is composed of five localities:<ref>{{cite web|title=Décret n° 84-365, fixant la composition, la consistance et les limites territoriale des communes. Wilaya d'El Oued|url=http://www.joradp.dz/JO8499/1984/067/FP1564.pdf|publisher=Journal officiel de la République Algérienne|access-date=2 March 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712065957/http://www.joradp.dz/JO8499/1984/067/FP1564.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-12 |page=1564 |language=fr |date=19 December 1984}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* Djamaa\n* [[Tigdidine]]\n* [[Ourglana]]\n* [[Sidi Yahia]]\n* [[Mazer Zaouia]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Algeria}}\n* [[Djema'a]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{-}}\n<div align=\"center\">'''Neighbouring towns and cities'''</div>\n{{Geographic location\n|Centre    = Djamaa\n|North     = '''[[Biskra]]'''<br>[[El M'Ghair]]<br>[[Tendla]]<br>[[Ourglana]]\n|Northeast = [[Hamraia]]\n|East      = [[Tigdidine]]<br>[[Reguiba]]<br>[[Guemar]]<br>'''[[El Oued]]'''\n|Southeast = [[Taibet]] ([[Ouargla Province|Ouargla]])\n|South     = [[Sidi Amrane]]<br>'''[[Touggourt]]'''\n|Southwest = '''[[Ouargla]]'''\n|West      = [[Sidi Yahia]]<br>[[M'Rara]]\n|Northwest = [[Ouled Djellal]] ([[Biskra Province|Biskra]])\n}}\n\n{{El M'Ghair Province}}\n\n[[Category:Communes of El M'Ghair Province]]"
