        "content": "{{Short description|Geologic formation in Austria}}\n{{Infobox rockunit\n| name           = Halobienschiefer Formation\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| type           = [[Formation (stratigraphy)|Formation]]\n| age            = [[Triassic]]\n| period         = Triassic\n| prilithology   = [[Shale]]\n| otherlithology =\n| namedfor       =\n| namedby        =\n| region         = \n| country        = Austria\n| coordinates    =\n| paleocoordinates    = \n| unitof         =\n| subunits       =\n| underlies      =\n| overlies       =\n| thickness      =\n| extent         =\n| area           =\n| map            =\n| map_caption    =\n}}\n\nThe '''Halobienschiefer Formation''' is a [[Formation (geology)|geologic formation]] in [[Austria]]. It preserves [[fossils]] dated to the [[Triassic]] [[Period (geology)|period]].\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Geology|Austria|Paleontology}}\n* [[List of fossiliferous stratigraphic units in Austria]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web|title= Fossilworks: Gateway to the Paleobiology Database|author= ((Various Contributors to the Paleobiology Database))|url= https://www.fossilworks.org|access-date= 17 December 2021|archive-date= 25 March 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220325060448/http://www.fossilworks.org/cgi-bin/bridge.pl?action=home|url-status= live}}\n\n[[Category:Triassic System of Europe]]\n[[Category:Triassic Austria]]\n[[Category:Shale formations]]\n\n{{Austria-geologic-formation-stub}}\n{{Triassic-stub}}"
