        "title": "Roy Moir",
        "content": "{{short description|Australian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=January 2016}}\n'''Albert Roy Moir''' (23 December 1897 &ndash; 16 September 1964) was an Australian politician who represented the [[South Australian House of Assembly]] seat of [[Electoral district of Norwood|Norwood]] from 1941 to 1944 and 1947 to 1953 for the [[Liberal and Country League]].<ref name=\"SA parl\">{{Cite SA-parl|pid=3685|name=Albert Roy Moir|former=yes|access-date=5 December 2022}}</ref>\n\nIn local politics, he served as mayor of the [[City of Kensington and Norwood|Town of Kensington and Norwood]] from 1946 to 1951.<ref name=b1986>{{Citation | author1=Matthews, Penny | title=South Australia, the civic record, 1836-1986 | year=1986 | publication-date=1986 | publisher=Wakefield Press | isbn=978-0-949268-82-2 |pages=250–255}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|au-sa-la}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Frank Nieass]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of Norwood|Norwood]] | years=1941&ndash;1944}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Frank Nieass]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Frank Nieass]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of Norwood|Norwood]] | years=1947&ndash;1953}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Don Dunstan]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moir, Albert}}\n[[Category:Members of the South Australian House of Assembly]]\n[[Category:1897 births]]\n[[Category:1964 deaths]]\n[[Category:Liberal and Country League politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Australian politicians]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in South Australia]]\n\n\n{{Australia-politician-stub}}"
