        "title": "Gerard Autet",
        "content": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2024}}\n{{family name hatnote|Autet|Serrabasa|lang=Spanish}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Gerard Autet\n| image = \n| fullname = Gerard Autet Serrabasa\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1978|9|8|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Manlleu]], [[Spain]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.86}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = \n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] \n| years1 = 1997–1998 | clubs1 = [[FC Barcelona C|Barcelona C]] | caps1 = 30 | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 1998–1999 | clubs2 = [[Palamós CF|Palamós]] | caps2 = 20 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 1999–2001 | clubs3 = [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] | caps3 = 31 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2001–2002 | clubs4 = [[Levante UD|Levante]] | caps4 = 34 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2002–2007 | clubs5 = [[Xerez CD|Xerez]] | caps5 = 134 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2007–2010 | clubs6 = [[Sporting de Gijón|Sporting Gijón]] | caps6 = 68 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2010–2012 | clubs7 = [[Xerez CD|Xerez]] | caps7 = 12 | goals7 = 0\n| totalcaps = 329 | totalgoals = 4\n| manageryears1 = 2012 | managerclubs1 = [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]] (assistant)\n}}\n'''Gerard Autet Serrabasa''' (born 8 September 1978) is a Spanish former [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nAutet was born in [[Manlleu]], [[Province of Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]]. During his early career, he played lower league football with [[Palamós CF]] and [[RCD Espanyol]]'s [[RCD Espanyol B|B team]]. He subsequently represented [[Levante UD]] and [[Xerez CD]], with both clubs competing in the [[Segunda División|second division]].\n\nAfter five seasons in [[Andalusia]], Autet signed with [[Sporting de Gijón]] for the [[2007–08 Segunda División|2007–08 season]], being an instrumental figure in the side's promotion to [[La Liga]]. His competition debut on 21 September 2008 was a sour one, as the [[Asturias|Asturians]] were crushed 1–6 at home against [[FC Barcelona]] and he was [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] before the hour-mark;<ref>[http://www.marca.com/marcador/futbol/2008_09/primera/jornada_3/spo_bar/ El Barça saca la cabeza en Gijón (Barça rear head in Gijón)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 21 September 2008 (in Spanish)</ref> he did contribute solidly in the club's [[2008–09 La Liga|narrow escape from relegation]], appearing in 26 games and scoring in a 2–1 home win over [[Málaga CF]] on 17 May 2009.<ref>[http://espnfc.com/uk/en/report/253053/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=5739 Sporting Gijón 2–1 Málaga]; [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]], 17 May 2009</ref>\n\nOnly third or fourth-string stopper in the [[2009–10 La Liga|2009–10 campaign]], Autet played only eight league matches, mainly due to suspensions or injuries to either [[Grégory Arnolin]] or [[Alberto Botía]]. He did start in all of those (seven complete) as Sporting again managed to retain their top-flight status.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|4533}}\n*{{Soccerway|gerard-autet-serrabasa/59226}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Autet, Gerard}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Osona]]\n[[Category:Footballers from the Province of Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Spanish men's footballers]]\n[[Category:Men's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda División players]]\n[[Category:Segunda División B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera División players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona C players]]\n[[Category:Palamós CF footballers]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol B footballers]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol footballers]]\n[[Category:Levante UD footballers]]\n[[Category:Xerez CD footballers]]\n[[Category:Sporting de Gijón players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Israel]]"
