        "content": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox stadium\n| name                = ِAluminium Stadium\n| nickname            = \n| logo_image          = \n| logo_caption        = \n| image               = Aluminium Stadium.jpg\n| image_size          = 220px\n| caption             = \n| fullname            = \n| former_names        = \n| location            = [[Nag Hammadi]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|26.007901|32.316623|display=inline,title}}\n| broke_ground        = \n| built               = \n| opened              = \n| renovated           = \n| expanded            = \n| closed              = \n| demolished          = \n| owner               = \n| operator            = \n| surface             = Grass\n| scoreboard          = \n| cost                = \n| architect           = \n| project_manager     = \n| structural engineer = \n| services engineer   = \n| general_contractor  = \n| main_contractors    = \n| capacity            = 16,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elgounafc.wordpress.com/grounds-of-egypt/naq-hammadi-estad-aluminium/|title = Naq Hammadi Estad Aluminium|date = 14 December 2009}}</ref>\n| suites              = \n| record_attendance   = \n| dimensions          = \n| acreage             = \n| tenants             = [[Aluminium Nag Hammâdi]]\n}}\n'''Aluminium Stadium''' ({{langx|ar|استاد الألومينيوم}}),  is located in '''Nag Hammadi''' ({{langx|ar|نجع حمادى}}), a city in [[Upper Egypt]]. It is the home ground for [[Aluminium Nag Hammâdi]], a football club competing in [[Egyptian Second Division]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Qena Governorate]]\n[[Category:Al Aluminium SC]]\n[[Category:Football venues in Egypt]]"
