        "title": "J. M. Raju",
        "content": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name         = John Mattupurathu Raju\n| native_name  =\n| image        =\n| caption      =\n| image_size   =\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1944|01|01|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Kochi]], Kerala, India\n| death_date   =\n| instrument   = Vocals\n| genre        = [[Playback singer|Playback singing]], [[Carnatic music]]\n| occupation   = Singer\n| years_active = 1962–1999\n| label        = Audiotracs\n| website      = \n}}\n'''John Mattupurathu Raju''' is an Indian film singer and music composer in [[Malayalam cinema]] during the 1970s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/profiles.php?i=572|title = JM Raju}}</ref> He made his debut with the movie ''[[Naadan Pennu]]'' in 1967.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.msidb.org/displayProfile.php?artist=JM%20Raju&category=singers|title=Profile of Malayalam Singer JM%20Raju}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRaju was born on 1 January 1944 in [[Ernakulam]], [[Kerala]], as the son of the late John Mattupurathu and the late Mary John. He is married to [[Latha Raju]], a Malayalam playback singer, who is the daughter of famous singers [[Santha P. Nair]] and [[K. Padmanabhan Nair]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/131211/entertainment-mollywood/article/born-sing|title = Born to sing|date = 11 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/the-kerala-connection/article4886546.ece|title=The Kerala connection|newspaper=The Hindu|date=6 July 2013|last1=M|first1=Athira}}</ref> The couple have two children, [[Aalap Raju]] and Anupama.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mathrubhuminews.in/ee/Programs/Episode/2808/generations-music-chakkarappanthal-episode-38/E |title=Mathrubhumi: Programs |website=mathrubhuminews.in |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814045440/http://mathrubhuminews.in/ee/Programs/Episode/2808/generations-music-chakkarappanthal-episode-38/E |archive-date=2014-08-14}} </ref> [[Aalap Raju]] is also a playback singer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/there-is-no-stopping-for-veteran-playback-singer-latha-raju/430431-71-210.html |title=There is no stopping for veteran playback singer Latha Raju |website=ibnlive.in.com |access-date=17 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131030142309/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/there-is-no-stopping-for-veteran-playback-singer-latha-raju/430431-71-210.html |archive-date=30 October 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Ready-for-Malayalam-acapella/articleshow/15137734.cms|title = Ready for Malayalam acapella? - Times of India|website = [[The Times of India]]| date=10 January 2017 }}</ref> In 2015 Raju won the Kalashree Award from the Kerala Sangeeta Nataka Academy.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===As a music composer===\n* Nadi Nadi ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\t\n* Bhaagyam vannu ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\t\n* Vaanil Vibhaatham ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\t\n* Kaathirunna Raavu ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\t\n* Kannaadikkaavilile ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\t\n* Navayuva Midhunam ...\tKeralam Manoharam\t1999\t\n* Anuraagame ...\tKeralam Manoharam\t1999\n* Prasada Sindooram ...\tKeralam Manoharam\t1999\t\n* Paalaruvi Neeyenikku Thozhi ...\tKeralam Manoharam\t1999\n\n===As a playback singer===\n* Naadan Premam ...\tNaadan Pennu\t1967\t\n* Paalkadal Naduvil ...\tKanaatha Veshangal\t1967\t\n* Raathri Raathri ...\tEzhu Raathrikal\t1968\t\n* Pottithakarnna ...\tBaalya Prathijna (Purusharathnam)\t1972\t\n* Marathakappattudutha Vilaasini ...\tBaalya Prathijna (Purusharathnam)\t1972\t\n* Kala kala mozhi ...\tPremageethangal\t1981\t\n* Ilam Manjil ...\tAdharangal Vithumpunnu\t1981\t\n* Ambili Manavatti azhakulla manavaatti ...\tEe Naadu\t1982\t\n* Thattedi Sosamme ...\tEe Naadu\t1982\t\n* Aakaasha perunthachan ...\tEe Naadu\t1982\t\n* Iru Meyyaanennaalum [Bit] ...\tEe Naadu\t1982\t\n* Amme mahaamaaye ...\tJambulingam\t1982\t\n* Amme Kanyaamariyame (Chilluvazhi Paayum) ...\tIdavela\t1982\t\n* Gloria Gloria Gloria Swargeeya (Vinnin Saanthi Sandesham) ...\tIdavela\t1982\t\n* Ente kadha ninte kadha ...\tIthu Njangalude Kadha\t1982\t\n* Thathammappenninu kalyaanam ...\tThuranna Jail\t1982\t\n* Swarga Vaathil Thurannu Thannu ...\tIniyenkilum\t1983\t\n* Ilam Manjil [Adharangal Vithumbunnu] ...\tKaathirunna Divasam\t1983\t\n* Poonkili painkili ...\tKolakkomban\t1983\t\n* Odi odi odi vannu ...\tSwanthamevide Bandhamevide\t1984\t\n* Illillam Poo ...\tAkalangalil\t1986\t\n* Bhaagyam vannu ...\tChevalier Michael\t1992\n\t\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|2364749}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Raju, J. M.}}\n[[Category:Malayalam playback singers]]\n[[Category:Singers from Kochi]]\n[[Category:Indian male playback singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male classical singers]]\n[[Category:Film musicians from Kerala]]\n[[Category:Male Carnatic singers]]\n[[Category:Carnatic singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian composers]]"
