        "title": "Jerseyempheria",
        "content": "{{Short description|Extinct genus of booklice}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| fossil_range = {{fossil_range|Cretaceous}}\n| genus = Jerseyempheria\n| parent_authority = Azar ''et al.'', 2010\n| species = grimaldii\n| authority = Azar ''et al.'', 2010\n}}\n\n'''''Jerseyempheria''''' is an extinct genus of empheriid [[psocodea]]n which existed in what is now [[New Jersey]] during the [[Cretaceous]] period.<ref name=Azar>{{Cite journal |author=Dany Azar |author2=André Nel |author3=Julian F. Petrulevicius |year=2010 |title=First Psocodean (Psocodea, Empheriidae) from the Cretaceous Amber of New Jersey|journal=Acta Geologica Sinica - English Edition |volume=84 |issue=4 |pages=762–767 |doi=10.1111/j.1755-6724.2010.00255.x|s2cid=129505225 |hdl=11336/242865 |hdl-access=free }}</ref> It was named by Dany Azar, André Nel and Julian F. Petrulevicius in [[2010 in paleontology|2010]], and the type species is ''Jerseyempheria grimaldii''.<ref name=Azar/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from1=Q21078881|from2=Q16754000}}\n\n[[Category:Psocoptera genera]]\n[[Category:Monotypic prehistoric insect genera]]\n[[Category:Cretaceous insects]]\n[[Category:Fossil taxa described in 2010]]\n[[Category:Prehistoric insects of North America]]\n[[Category:Trogiomorpha]]\n\n\n{{Psocoptera-stub}}\n{{cretaceous-insect-stub}}"
