        "title": "Cyclostremella concordia",
        "content": "{{Short description|Species of gastropod}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cyclostremella concordia\n| authority = [[Paul Bartsch|Bartsch]], 1920\n| synonyms_ref = \n| synonyms = \n}}\n\n'''''Cyclostremella concordia''''' is a [[species]] of [[sea snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Pyramidellidae]], the pyrams and their allies. The species is one of three known species to exist within the genus, ''[[Cyclostremella]]''. The other species being ''[[Cyclostremella humilis]]'' and ''[[Cyclostremella orbis]]''.<ref name=\"WoRMS\">Rosenberg, G. (2011). ''Cyclostremella concordia'' Bartsch, 1920. Accessed through:  [[World Register of Marine Species]] at http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=581088 on 2011-10-26</ref><ref>Turgeon, D.; Quinn, J.F.; Bogan, A.E.; Coan, E.V.; Hochberg, F.G.; Lyons, W.G.; Mikkelsen, P.M.; Neves, R.J.; Roper, C.F.E.; Rosenberg, G.; Roth, B.; Scheltema, A.; Thompson, F.G.; Vecchione, M.; Williams, J.D. (1998). Common and scientific names of aquatic invertebrates from the United States and Canada: mollusks. 2nd ed. American Fisheries Society Special Publication, 26. American Fisheries Society: Bethesda, MD (USA). {{ISBN|1-888569-01-8}}. IX, 526 + cd-rom pp.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=581088 World Register of Marine Species]\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3174477}}\n\n[[Category:Pyramidellidae]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 1920]]\n\n\n{{Pyramidellidae-stub}}"
