        "title": "Martonvásár District",
        "content": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Martonvásár District\n| native_name            = <small>''Martonvásári járás''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = Coa Hungary Town Martonvásár.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Martonvásári járás.png\n|map_caption          = Martonvásár District within Hungary and Fejér County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Fejér County|Fejér]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Martonvásár]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = {{Coord|47.31|18.79|display=inline,title}}\n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 277.13\n| area_rank              = [[Fejér County#Regional structure|8th in Fejér]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 28,040\n|population_rank         = [[Fejér County#Regional structure|7th in Fejér]]\n|population_density_km2  = 101\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Martonvásár''' ({{langx|hu|Martonvásári járás}}) is a district in eastern part of [[Fejér County]]. ''[[Martonvásár]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Central Transdanubia|Central Transdanubia Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nMartonvásár District borders with [[Bicske District]] to the north, [[Érd District]] and [[Ráckeve District]] ''([[Pest County]])'' to the east, [[Dunaújváros District]] to the south, [[Gárdony District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Martonvásár District is '''8'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''6''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2012)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2012.xls A KSH 2012. évi helységnévkönyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Baracska]] (2,766)\n*'''[[Ercsi]]''' (7,999)\n*[[Gyúró]] (1,254)\n*[[Kajászó]] (1,055)\n*'''[[Martonvásár]]''' (5,811) – district seat\n*[[Ráckeresztúr]] (3,311)\n*[[Tordas]] (2,123)\n*[[Vál]] (2,521)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns in Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/martonvasari-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Martonvásár District]\n\n{{Martonvásár District}}\n{{Districts of Fejér County}}\n\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Fejér County]]\n\n\n{{Fejer-geo-stub}}"
