        "title": "Slobodan Topalović",
        "content": "{{short description|Serbian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Slobodan Topalović\n| image = \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = 8 November 1952\n| birth_place = [[Čačak]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| death_date = 1 May 1994\n| death_place = [[Belgrade]], [[FR Yugoslavia]]\n| height = 191cm\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 1974&ndash;1977 \n| years2 = 1977&ndash;1979 \n| years3 = 1979&ndash;1981 \n| years4 = 1981&ndash;1987\n| clubs1 = [[1. FC Köln]] \n| clubs2 = [[Viktoria Köln]] \n| clubs3 = [[OFK Belgrade]] \n| clubs4 = [[Olympique Lyonnais]]\n| caps1 = 17  \n| goals1 = 0 \n| nationalyears1 = 1978&ndash;1985\n| nationalteam1 = [[Yugoslavia]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n\n'''Slobodan Topalović''' (8 November 1952 &ndash; May 1994) was a Serbian [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]]. He is considered to be one of [[Olympique Lyonnais]] best ever goalkeepers and has been named the best ever Yugoslavian to associate with the club. His son was also a professional footballer who played in Iran, Kazakhstan, Serbia and is now a goalkeeping coach for [[Emirates Club]]. Slobodan played in [[West Germany]], before having a stint of two years with [[OFK Belgrade]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hr.nogonet.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=354&Itemid=96|title=1.liga 1980/81.|accessdate=2008-04-23|publisher=nogonet}}{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He then ended his career with [[Olympique Lyonnais]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{WorldFootball.net|slobodan-topalovic}}\n*{{Fussballdaten|topalovicslobodan}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Topalovic, Slobodan}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:1994 deaths]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav men's footballers]]\n[[Category:Serbian men's footballers]]\n[[Category:1. FC Köln players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:OFK Beograd players]]\n[[Category:Olympique Lyonnais players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Čačak]]\n[[Category:FC Viktoria Köln players]]\n[[Category:Men's association football goalkeepers]]\n\n\n{{Serbia-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}"
