        "content": "{{Short description|American politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = \n| name         =Mike Millican\n| honorific-suffix = \n| image        =   \n| alt          = \n| state_house  =Alabama\n| district     =17th\n| term_start   =1990\n| term_end     =2018\n| predecessor  = \n| successor    = [[Tracy Estes]]\n| prior_term   =\n| birth_date   ={{birth date and age|1950|12|5}}\n| birth_place  =[[Sulligent, Alabama]], United States\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| profession   = \n| religion= \n| party=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] (before 2010)<br>[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] (2010-present)\n}}\n\n'''Michael J. Millican''' (born December 5, 1950) was an [[American people|American]] politician. He was a member of the [[Alabama House of Representatives]] from the 17th District, serving from 1990 to 2018. He is a member of the Republican party.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mike Millican Political Profile|url=https://www.bamapolitics.com/alabama/alabama-government-officials/profiles/mike-millican/|access-date=2020-06-22|website=Bama Politics|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Alabama House of Representatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Millican, Mike}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the Alabama House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:People from Sulligent, Alabama]]\n[[Category:21st-century American legislators]]\n[[Category:21st-century Alabama politicians]]\n\n\n{{Alabama-politician-stub}}"
