        "title": "Monica Wofford",
        "content": "{{Short description|American business executive}}\n{{like resume|date=January 2024}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Monica L. Wofford\n| image = Monical Wofford.jpg\n| caption = Wofford as the keynote speaker for the Florida Tax Collectors Association \n| birth_date =  \n| birth_place =  \n| nationality =  American\n| occupation = CEO, consultant, speaker, author\n| known_for =    \n| alma_mater = \n| years_active =  \n| title =  \n| website = [http://www.contagiouscompanies.com/ Contagious Companies]\n}}\n'''Monica L. Wofford''', CSP, is an American business executive and founder of Contagious Companies.<ref>[https://s3.amazonaws.com/contagious/pdf/MH_ADolphinOutofWater_WoffordM.pdf \"A Dolphin Out of Water\"] ''Miami Herald''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref><ref>[http://www.torontosun.com/2016/04/06/quirky-questions \"Quirky questions\"] ''Toronto Sun''. Retrieved 2016-10-03.</ref>\n\nBefore founding the [[training]] and consulting firm, Contagious Companies, in 2003, Wofford began her [[motivational speaker|speaking]] and training career in 1989 with her first [[keynote]] to 9000 fellow students. She has worked with leadership teams in companies such as the [[US Mint]], the Transportation and Safety Administration, the [[FAA]], [[SHRM]], Hallmark, Combined Insurance, AT&T, Estee Lauder, the Non-Profit Times, Cabela's, Microsoft, and SeaWorld. She has spoken or trained in all 50 states and 27 countries<ref>[http://www.canadianchiropractor.ca/leadership/parker-university-exec-calls-for-social-movement-for-chiropractors-2759 \"Parker University exec calls for “social movement” for chiropractors\"] ''Canadian Chiropractors''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> for events<ref>[http://www.ocala.com/news/20180305/international-womens-day-celebration-on-thursday \"International Women’s Day Celebration on Thursday\"] ''Ocala StarBanner''. Retrieved 2018-04-02.</ref> and organizations including [[TED Talks]],<ref>[http://www.ocala.com/news/20160922/tedxocala-is-back-for-more \"TEDxOcala is back for more\"] ''Ocala StarBanner''. Retrieved 2016-10-03.</ref> the Association of Corporate Contributions Professionals,<ref>[http://www.accprof.org/ACCP/Learning/ACCP__The_Conference/2017_Speakers/ACCP/Learning/ACCP__The_Conference/Speakers.aspx?hkey=5441b398-b230-4b4f-8dc7-2149f9ea5118 \"Meet our 2017 Conference Speakers\"] ACCP. Retrieved 2017-04-27.</ref> and the Association of Legal Administrators.<ref>[http://www.alanet.org/ac2017/speakers/speaker-directory \"Speaker Directory\"] ALANet. Retrieved 2017-04-27.</ref>\n\nHer expertise is often requested by the media and magazines such as ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]'',<ref>[http://fortune.com/2012/08/02/when-you-are-a-beloved-employees-replacement/ \"When you are a beloved employee's replacement\"] ''Fortune''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> ''Forbes'',<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130130004223/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/47296180/ns/business-forbes_com/t/yes-your-boss-crazy-heres-how-deal/#.VqU3YmQrKKs \"Yes your boss is crazy. Here's how to deal.\"] ''[[Forbes]]''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> ''CNBC'',<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/2012/05/03/make-difficult-people-disappear-new-book-on-eliminating-office-conflict.html \"‘Make Difficult People Disappear’ — New Book on Eliminating Office Conflict\"] ''CNBC''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> the ''Toronto Sun'',<ref>[http://contagious.s3.amazonaws.com/pdf/SignsYoureGoingtoGetFiredbyMonicaWofford.pdf \"Impending Job Doom\"] ''Toronto Sun''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> ''Miami Herald'', ''Entrepreneur'' magazine,<ref>[http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/224946?fb_ref=fbrec \"6 Simple Solutions for Getting Rid of Stress\"] ''Entrepreneur''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> ''CNN Headline News'',<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eur7ehKq3HI \"Cell phones and rude people\"] ''CNN Headline News''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> ''Bloomberg Businessweek'' and ''U.S. News''.<ref>[http://money.usnews.com/money/careers/articles/2013/10/10/are-you-on-the-verge-of-being-fired \"Are You on the Verge of Being Fired?\"] ''U.S. News''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref>\n\nShe is the author of six books,<ref>[http://newsok.com/author-monica-wofford-says-board-games-teach-us-a-lot-about-others/article/3939855 \"Author Monica Wofford says board games teach us a lot about others\"] ''The Oklahoman''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref><ref>[https://s3.amazonaws.com/contagious/pdf/oddball_interview_questions.pdf \"Oddball Interview Questions\"] ''Toronto Sun''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref>  including ''Make Difficult People Disappear: How to Deal with Stressful Behavior and Eliminate Conflict''<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2012-12-13/homelands-carrie-mathison-workplace-hero \"'Homeland's Carrie Mathison, Workplace Hero\"] ''Bloomberg Businessweek''. Retrieved 2016-02-04.</ref> and ''Contagious Leadership''.\n\nShe is a board member and national treasurer of the [[National Speakers Association]].<ref>[http://www.tennessean.com/story/money/tech/2015/07/05/social-media-can-take-public-speaking-next-level/29621849/ \"Social media can take public speaking to next level\"] ''Tennessean''. Retrieved 2016-02-28.</ref>\n\nOn 1 September 2017, Wofford filed to run for the [[Florida House of Representatives]] in District 32, which includes most of [[Lake County, Florida|Lake County]].<ref>[http://floridapolitics.com/archives/244109-professional-speaker-monica-wofford-joins-race-house-district-32 \"Professional speaker Monica Wofford joins race for House District 32\"] ''Florida Politics''. Retrieved 2018-03-13.</ref> She qualified for the ballot by petition in March 2018.<ref>[http://floridapolitics.com/archives/259997-in-hd-32-monica-wofford-qualifies-for-ballot-by-petition \"In HD 32, Monica Wofford qualifies for ballot by petition\"] ''Florida Politics''. Retrieved 2018-04-02.</ref>{{needs update|date=January 2024}}\n\nFrom 2020 to 2022, she served as the CEO of United Way of Lake & Sumter Counties.<ref>[https://www.dailycommercial.com/story/news/nonprofits/2022/02/20/united-way-lake-and-sumter-counties-ceo-talks-new-programs-whats-ahead/6812008001/ \"‘Not your average United Way’: CEO talks new programs, expanding their reach and what's ahead\"] ''Daily Commercial''. Retrieved 2022-02-22.</ref><ref>[https://www.leesburg-news.com/2022/05/03/united-way-recognizes-hometown-heroes/ \"United Way recognizes Hometown Heroes\"] ''Leesburg-News''. Retrieved 2022-06-13.</ref><ref>[https://www.wftv.com/news/local/lake-county/united-way-donates-225k-23-lake-sumter-county-non-profits/QPLLPAYT6ZEAZDK4PPFCTJNS34/ \"United Way donates $225K to 23 Lake, Sumter county non-profits\"] ''WFTV''. Retrieved 2024-09-20.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.monicawofford.com Monica Wofford, CSP] Official site\n* [http://www.contagiouscompanies.com/ Contagious Companies]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TFRfuG3e4Zc \"When Did We All Become Difficult People?\"] TEDxOcala\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wofford, Monica}}\n[[Category:American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]"
