        "title": "Krishnai River",
        "content": "{{short description|River in India}}\n{{Infobox river\n| name                = Krishnai River\n| native_name         ={{native name|as|কৃষ্ণাই নদী}}\n| name_other          = \n| name_etymology      = \n| nickname            = \n<!---------------------- IMAGE-->\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| image_caption       = \n| image_alt           = \n<!---------------------- MAPS -->\n| map                 = \n| map_size            = \n| map_caption         = \n| map_alt             = \n| pushpin_map         = India Assam#India\n| pushpin_map_size    = \n| pushpin_map_caption = \n| pushpin_map_alt     = \n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1   = State\n| subdivision_name1   = [[Meghalaya]] &  [[Assam]]\n| subdivision_type2   = \n| subdivision_name2   = \n| subdivision_type3   = \n| subdivision_name3   = \n| subdivision_type4   = \n| subdivision_name4   = \n| subdivision_type5   = \n| subdivision_name5   = \n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length              = \n| width_min           = \n| width_avg           = \n| width_max           = \n| depth_min           = \n| depth_avg           = \n| depth_max           = \n| discharge1_location = \n| discharge1_min      = \n| discharge1_avg      = \n| discharge1_max      = \n<!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES -->\n| source1             = [[West Garo Hills]]\n| source1_location    = [[Meghalaya]]\n| source1_coordinates = {{coord|25.6209436|N|90.3620221|E|display=inline}}\n| source1_elevation   = \n| mouth               = Mornoi River\n| mouth_location      = \n| mouth_coordinates   = {{coord|26|04|30.1|N|90|45|16.8|E|display=inline}}\n| mouth_elevation     = \n| progression         = Krishnai River - Dudhnoi River – Mornoi River - [[Brahmaputra River]]\n| river_system        = \n| basin_size          = \n| basin_landmarks     = \n| basin_population    = \n| tributaries_left    = \n| tributaries_right   = \n| waterbodies         = \n| waterfalls          = \n| bridges             = \n| ports               = \n| custom_label        = \n| custom_data         = \n| extra               = \n}}\nThe '''Krishnai River''' is a sub-[[tributary]] of the [[Brahmaputra River]] in the Indian state of [[Assam]]. The Krishnai River originates in the [[West Garo Hills]] of [[Meghalaya]]. The Krishnai River meets [[Dudhnoi River]] at Matia of [[Goalpara district]] and then flows as [[Mornoi River]] before its confluence with the [[Brahmaputra River]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cgwb.gov.in/District_Profile/Assam/Goalpara.pdf|website=Goalpara district profile|title=Ground Water Information Booklet Goalpara District, Assam|language=en|access-date=27 September 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Rivers of Assam]]\n\n\n{{India-river-stub}}"
