        "title": "Epichorista siriana",
        "content": "{{Short description|Species of moth}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| image = Epichorista siriana 59267897.jpg\n| image_caption = \n| image2 = \n| image2_caption = \n| status = \n| status_system = \n| genus = Epichorista\n| species = siriana\n| authority = ([[Edward Meyrick|Meyrick]], 1881)<ref>[http://www.tortricidae.com/catalogueGenusList.asp?gcode=365 tortricidae.com]</ref>\n| synonyms = *''Tortrix siriana'' <small>Meyrick, 1881</small>\n*''Proselena siriana''\n}}\n\n'''''Epichorista siriana''''' is a species of [[moth]] of the family [[Tortricidae]]. It is found in [[New Zealand]].\n\nThe [[wingspan]] is 10.5–12&nbsp;mm for males and about 14&nbsp;mm for females. The forewings deep brownish ochreous, mixed with dark fuscous in males. The hindwings are blackish. In female, the forewings are reddish ochreous, with a few dark fuscous scales. The hindwings of the females are whitish.<ref>[http://rsnz.natlib.govt.nz/volume/rsnz_15/rsnz_15_00_001010.html Transactions and Proceedings of the Royal Society of New Zealand 1868-1961, Volume 15, 1882] {{PD-notice}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons}}\n{{Wikispecies}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q13609343}}\n\n[[Category:Moths described in 1881]]\n[[Category:Epichorista]]\n[[Category:Moths of New Zealand]]\n\n\n{{Archipini-stub}}"
