        "content": "{{Infobox restaurant\n| embed               = \n| name                = Mido Cafe\n| title               = <!-- If embedding use this for secondary small font title -->\n| logo                = \n| logo_width          = \n| logo_alt            = \n| image               = \n| image_width         = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       = \n| mapframe            = yes \n| pushpin_map         = <!-- Requires {{para|coordinates}} -->\n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| map_size            = \n| slogan              = \n| established         = 1950\n| closed              = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| current-owner       = \n| previous-owner      = \n| head-chef           = \n| chef                = \n| pastry-chef         = \n| food-type           = \n| dress-code          = \n| rating              = \n| street-address      = 63 Temple Street, Yau Ma Tei\n| city                = \n| county              = \n| state               = \n| postcode            = <!-- or |zip= -->\n| country             =  [[Hong Kong]]\n| coordinates         = <!-- {{coord}} -->\n| seating-capacity    = \n| reservations        = \n| other-locations     = \n| other-information   = <!-- or |other-label= -->\n| website             = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}\n{{multiple image\n | align = right\n | total_width = 320\n | image_style = border:none;\n\n | image1 = Mido Cafe 202011.jpg\n | caption1 = Mido Cafe in 2020.\n\n | image2 = HK YMT 油麻地 Yau Ma Tei 上海街 Shanghai Street 眾坊街 Public Square Street 美都餐室 Mido Cafe March 2020 SS2 08.jpg\n | caption2 = Ground floor of Mido Cafe in 2020.\n}}\n[[File:MidoCafe Upper1.jpg|thumb|Upper floor of Mido Cafe in 2006.]]\n'''Mido Cafe''' ({{zh|t=美都餐室}}) is a [[cha chaan teng]] and [[bing sutt]] located No. 63 [[Temple Street, Hong Kong|Temple Street]], at the corner of [[Public Square Street]], in [[Yau Ma Tei]], [[Kowloon]], [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"time out\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timeout.com/hong-kong/restaurants/mido-cafe  |title=Mido Cafe |last= |first= |date=20 July 2020 |website= |publisher=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]] Hong Kong |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref name=\"thugs\">{{cite news |last=Lo |first=Clifford |date=6 August 2013 |title=Thugs sought after Hong Kong's old Mido Cafe trashed  |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1294493/more-10-men-sought-after-one-citys-oldest-cafes-trashed |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |location= |access-date=}}</ref>\n\nMido Cafe was established in 1950.<ref name=\"time out\"/><ref name=\"thugs\"/> It occupies the ground and first floor of a four-storey concrete building, and has retained a number of original features, such as wood booths and floor and wall tiles of that era.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.epd.gov.hk/eia/register/report/eiareport/eia_2082013/2_EIA/PDF/Appendix/Volume%207/Appendix%2012.1.pdf |title=Central Kowloon Route EIA Study. Appendix 12.1. Built Heritage Catalogue |last= |first= |date=January 2013 |website= |publisher=[[Environmental Protection Department]] |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nIt suddenly closed on July 18, 2022 via a letter on the door, which did not specify if this was a temporary closure or a permanent closure.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chan |first=Cherry |title=Mido Cafe bids farewell for now to Yau Ma Tei neighbourhood |url=https://www.timeout.com/hong-kong/news/mido-cafe-bids-farewell-for-now-to-yau-ma-tei-neighbourhood-071822 |access-date=2022-07-19 |website=Time Out Hong Kong |language=en-GB}}</ref> After a pause of three months, the restaurant reopened its doors for business on October 28, 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kong |first=Dimsumdaily Hong |date=2022-10-28 |title=Historical Mido Cafe which closed down in July reopens today to the surprise of netizens |url=https://www.dimsumdaily.hk/historical-mido-cafe-which-closed-down-in-july-reopens-today-to-the-surprise-of-netizens/ |access-date=2023-06-27 |website=Dimsum Daily |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Leung |first=Jenny |date=2022-11-05 |title=Mido Cafe reopens in Yau Ma Tei following temporary closure |url=https://www.timeout.com/hong-kong/news/mido-cafe-reopens-in-yau-ma-tei-following-temporary-closure-071822 |access-date=2023-06-27 |website=Time Out Hong Kong |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-17 |title=Back on the menu: Hong Kong’s iconic Mido Cafe opens again after brief hiatus |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/people-culture/article/3203112/back-menu-hong-kong-culinary-icon-returns-mido-cafe-reopens-its-doors-keep-city-touch-tradition |access-date=2023-06-27 |website=South China Morning Post |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIt has been featured in several films and TV shows, including ''[[The World of Suzie Wong (film)|The World of Suzie Wong]]'' (1960),<ref name=\"time out\"/> ''[[Days of Being Wild]]'' (1990),<ref name=\"tatler\">{{cite web |url=https://hk.asiatatler.com/life/5-iconic-movie-locations-in-hong-kong |title=5 Iconic Movie Locations To Visit In Hong Kong |last=Yu |first=Helen |date=17 September 2019 |publisher=[[Asia Tatler]] }}</ref> ''[[Moonlight Express]]'' (1999),<ref name=\"time out\"/> ''[[Street Fighters]]'',<ref name=\"time out\"/> ''[[Goodbye Mr. Cool]]'' (2001),<ref name=\"tatler\"/>  ''[[Revolving Doors of Vengeance]]'' (2005),<ref name=\"time out\"/> ''[[Strangers (2018 TV series)|Strangers]]'' (2018).\n\n==See also==\n* [[China Cafe]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Mido Cafe}}\n* [https://www.ladyironchef.com/2017/09/mido-cafe-hong-kong/ Review with pictures] at ladyironchef.com\n\n{{coord|22.31024|114.17032|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Restaurants in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Yau Ma Tei]]\n\n{{HongKong-stub}}"
